{
  "text": "Peripheral blood mononuclear cells (PBMCs) were prepared in RPMI 1640 medium containing 10% fetal calf serum (FCS) (RPMI Advances in Hematology 3 1640/FCS, Invitrogen Ltd.) as described previously [CITATION_1] . PBMCs (0.5 \u00d7 10 5 ) in 200 l of RPMI 1640/FCS were added to each well of a 96-well round-bottomed plate and incubated for 8-10 days with 10 mol of one of the following: Sp17(1), Sp17(2), Sp17(3), Sp17(4), Sp17(5), Sp17(6), or the control HIV peptides, 10 g/ml phytohaemagglutinin (PHA; SigmaAldrich Co. Ltd., Dorset, UK), or tissue culture media only. Recombinant interleukin-2 (rIL-2: 20 iu/ml; Roche Diagnostics, Indianapolis, IN, USA) and rIL-7 (25 ng/ml; R&D Systems, Minneapolis, MN, USA) were added on days 2, 5, and 7.",
